<br>
Play what you want, play what's fun for you. But also consider the fact that if you and your RL friend end up on opposite sides of the good/evil spectrum, then:<br>
<br>
1) you cannot group together<br>
2) you will likely start out in very distant continents<br>
3) you likely will have major language barriers in the game<br>
<br>
You need to discuss this with your friend. The best thing to do is for BOTH of you to come to a consensus on which 2 character types you will both play. Hopefully both of your characters will be of similar alignment so that makes it much easier for grouping as well as other cultural compatibility purposes. <br>
<br>
For example, if one of you ends up being High Elf and the other one chooses to play a Troll..... ummm you're going to have major major problems being able to play together (at least initially). <br>
<br>
